  <sect1 id="intro">
    <title>Introduction</title>
    <para>
      Each person who uses a Linux/Unix system has the ability to be given a
      user.  The user account allows them to configure their own preferences,
      secure their private work from others, and even let them have their
      desktop look entirely different from the person using the same computer on
      another user account.  This however isn't a very easy task to do for an
      administrator with lots of users.  The Users and Groups tool in Ximian
      Setup Tools strives to make this experience easier for administrators.
    </para>
  </sect1>

